here is grain\nenvugh in sight to keep tho ma\nchine going two months longer.\nJoe Busch went to Paeblo last\nSaturday might with a view of get\nting work all winter at his trade,\nbut when he teached the big town\nbe found the panmic preceded him\nand s 0 came back to Monte Vista\nThursday morning and says bis\nJather\u2019s family will also return\nbere next week. The Busches are\nfirst class painters and paper hang\nors and we hope their old custom\nors will take notice that they are\nbere again for husiness.\n1f you buy an Edwon Phono\ngrspb you will be bappy.\nW. H. PooLx.\nThrough By Private Train\nTour of all Mexico via OColorado\nSouthern leaves Denver January\n98 Full information on request.\nT. E. Fisber, G P A, Denver\nA Nard Dopt to Pay.\n1 owe a debt of gratitude that ean\naover be paud off,\u201d writes Q. 8. Olark, of\nWestfield, Jowa, \u201cfor my resoue from\ndeath, by Dr. Kings New Discovery.\nBeth lungs were s 0 seriowsly affected\nthat death ssomed Imminment, when\n1 commenced taking New Discov.\n\"oty. The ominous dry, haoking cough\nquit before the firet botile was wsed, and\ntwo more botties made complete oure.\u201d\nNothiag has ever equalled New Discov\ney for cougha, colds and all throat and\nleag complaints. Guatantesd bv all\ndragpets. 808 aad 1.00. Trial bottle fres.\nThe beat miyor of the best gov\nerned city in -he United States\u2014\nTom Johnson- -was reelected may\nor of Cleveler, Ohio, Tuesday by\na majority of ibout 10,000. Con\n|gressman Burton was the oppos\ning candidate and was supported\nby all the trusts and backed by the\nadministration. The issue was\nlargely a question of municipal\nownership of the street railroads,\n|(but party hines were as closely\n|drawn as it was poesible. Cleve\nland 18 the largest city in thg atate.\nThis ia Mayor Johnson\u2019s fourth\nterm.\nBusiness at the Del Norte land\noffice was exceptionally good dur\ning October. During the month\n14 bomestead entries covering\n2,248 acres and 10 desert e